06/06/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the European People's Party (EPP) group gathered on Saturday (June 5th) at a conference in Sarajevo to discuss co-operation and EU integration. In a joint statement they voiced support for the EU perspective for all countries from the region. The participants also stressed that perpetrators of war crimes should be brought to justice. The conference, organised by the Party of Democratic Action (SDA) and the EPP, brought together representatives of political parties from BiH, Serbia, Slovenia and Croatia. (Fena, BHRT, RTRS, Radio Free Europe - 05/06/10)
